  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main goal of this study is to determine the association between:

        -  the quantity of mother's milk and duration of breastfeeding

        -  the intake of polyunsaturated fatty acids and iron during hospitalization and the
           development of preterm infants born with a GA &lt; 32 weeks.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
